(
<emphasis box="[279,307,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[322,389,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">dorud</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sama, G. &amp; Rapuzzi, P. &amp; Rejzek, M." box="[404,604,1087,1113]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" pagination="163 - 179" refId="ref2932" refString="Sama, G., Rapuzzi, P. &amp; Rejzek, M. (2007) New or interesting Phytoeciini from the Middle East, especially from Iran (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). Folia Heyrovskyana (A), 14, 163 - 179." type="journal article" year="2007">
Sama 
<emphasis box="[474,530,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">et al.</emphasis>
, 2007
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[623,703,1087,1113]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">stat. n.</emphasis>
was originally described as subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sama, Rapuzzi &amp; Rejzek, 2007" authorityName="Sama, Rapuzzi &amp; Rejzek" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Helladia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="imperials" subSpecies="dorud">
<emphasis box="[1152,1436,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Helladia imperials dorud</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sama, G. &amp; Rapuzzi, P. &amp; Rejzek, M." box="[151,506,1123,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" pagination="163 - 179" refId="ref2932" refString="Sama, G., Rapuzzi, P. &amp; Rejzek, M. (2007) New or interesting Phytoeciini from the Middle East, especially from Iran (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). Folia Heyrovskyana (A), 14, 163 - 179." type="journal article" year="2007">Sama, Rapuzzi &amp; Rejzek, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; although it is strongly different from 
<taxonomicName authority="Sama &amp; Rejzek, 2001" authorityName="Sama &amp; Rejzek" authorityYear="2001" box="[936,1401,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phytoecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imperialis" subGenus="Helladia">
<emphasis box="[936,974,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Ph.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[990,1018,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1034,1148,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">imperialis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sama, G. &amp; Rejzek, M." box="[1155,1401,1123,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" pagination="239 - 246" refId="ref2979" refString="Sama, G. &amp; Rejzek, M. (2001) Helladia imperalis, espece nouvelle de l'Iran (Col., Cerambycidae, Phytoeciini). Biocosme Mesogeen, 17 (3), 239 - 246." type="journal article" year="2001">Sama &amp; Rejzek, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the darker body, antennae and legs; the black elytra, which look glabrous because of very short pubescence; and the pronotum pale area densely covered with pale recumbent pubescence. So, we propose that 
<taxonomicName authority="Sama, et al., 2007" box="[1161,1325,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Phytoecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorud" subGenus="Helladia">
<emphasis box="[1161,1199,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">Ph.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1215,1243,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1258,1325,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">dorud</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Sama, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">et al.</emphasis>
, 2007), 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[273,354,1231,1257]" pageId="2" pageNumber="593">stat. n.</emphasis>
must be elevated to a species rank.
</paragraph>
